Returns: The start time in nanoseconds or @B_android#view#FrameStats#UNDEFINED_TIME_NANO_E@ if there is no frame data.
getStartTimeNano().Description: Gets the start time of the interval for which these statistics apply. The start interval is the time when the first frame was presented.

getRefreshPeriodNano().Description: Gets the refresh period of the display hosting the window(s) for which these statistics apply.

Returns: The end time in nanoseconds or @B_android#view#FrameStats#UNDEFINED_TIME_NANO_E@ if there is no frame data.
getEndTimeNano().Description: Gets the end time of the interval for which these statistics apply. The end interval is the time when the last frame was presented.

getFrameCount().Description: Gets the number of frames for which there is data.

Returns: The presented time in nanoseconds or @B_android#view#FrameStats#UNDEFINED_TIME_NANO_E@ if the frame is not presented yet.
getFramePresentedTimeNano(int).Description: Get the time a frame at a given index was presented.

ClassDesc: This is the base class for frame statistics.
